# Vercel Environment Variables — Maison Douceur + Supabase

## Frontend (VITE_* — embedded at build time)

| Variable | Example |
|----------|---------|
| `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` | `https://fipsclbgsrjldhtdaumj.supabase.co` |
| `VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` | `sb_publishable_...` |
| `VITE_SITE_URL` | `https://cake-jade-two.vercel.app` |
| `VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` | Stripe publishable key (`pk_test_...` or `pk_live_...`) |
| `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` | Stripe secret key — **server only**, never `VITE_` |
| `VITE_API_URL` | Optional PHP API URL |

## Server-side only (never use VITE_ prefix)

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `DATABASE_URL` | PostgreSQL connection string |
| `SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY` | Admin/server operations |
| `SUPABASE_JWKS_URL` | JWT verification |

## Setup Supabase database

1. Open [Supabase Dashboard](https://supabase.com/dashboard) → your project
2. Go to **SQL Editor**
3. Paste and run `backend/migrations/supabase.sql`
4. Redeploy Vercel: `vercel --prod`

## Local development

```bash
vercel env pull .env.local
npm run dev
```
